## 🔁 Relational / Comparison Operators

Used in conditions (inside `[ ]` brackets):

| Operator | Meaning | Numeric | String |
|---|---|---|---|
| Equal | Equals | `-eq` | `==` |
| Not Equal | Not equals | `-ne` | `!=` |
| Greater Than | Greater | `-gt` | `>` |
| Less Than | Lesser | `-lt` | `<` |
| Greater or Equal | GTE | `-ge` | `>=` |
| Less or Equal | LTE | `-le` | `<=` |

```bash
#!/bin/bash

A=15
B=20

if [ $A -eq $B ]; then
  echo "A equals B"
elif [ $A -gt $B ]; then
  echo "A is greater"
else
  echo "B is greater"
fi
```

