## 🔗 Logical Operators

| Operator | Symbol | Meaning |
|---|---|---|
| AND | `&&` | Both conditions true |
| OR | `\|\|` | At least one condition true |
| NOT | `!` | Negates condition |

```bash
#!/bin/bash

AGE=25
INCOME=50000

# AND condition
if [ $AGE -ge 18 ] && [ $INCOME -ge 30000 ]; then
  echo "Eligible for loan"
else
  echo "Not eligible"
fi
```

