## 🌍 Real-World Usage

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A["Check Disk Usage\n$(df -h | awk '{print $5}')"] --> B{Usage > 80%?}
    B -- Yes --> C["Send Alert Email"]
    B -- No --> D["Log: Disk OK"]

    style B fill:#F7931E,color:#fff
    style C fill:#E74C3C,color:#fff
    style D fill:#4EAA25,color:#fff
```

```bash
#!/bin/bash
# Real-world: Disk usage alert script

USAGE=$(df / | tail -1 | awk '{print $5}' | tr -d '%')
THRESHOLD=80

echo "Current Disk Usage: $USAGE%"

if [ $USAGE -ge $THRESHOLD ]; then
  echo "⚠️  WARNING: Disk usage is above ${THRESHOLD}%!"
else
  echo "✅ Disk usage is normal."
fi
```

